main event: A civilian reported observing a UFO in Tampa, Florida during a three-hour and ten-minute period on October 17-18, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as a circle of white light with bright exterior lights., The first UFO, termed the mother ship, shot out a flash of green light., Ten donut-shaped UFOs were also reported, alternating colors of red, yellow, and green., The witness used binoculars for observation., Local astronomers had reported seeing the satellite Geopaus and the planet Jupiter around the same time.
sighted object: a circle of white light and ten donut-shaped UFOs
witness description: civilian housewife from Tampa, described as rational and sincere
